column1: #     This table contains the sources identified as possible gravitational lens candidates based on an analysis of the observations in the neighbourhoud of a list of sources selected from a compilation of quasar candidates. Information about the catalogues from which these quasars proceed is given in the table of lens catalogue names.

column2: a list of components found around that source is tabulated
column3: together with some information about their position and flux as derived from the cluster of observations associated with each of them. These individual observations are provided in \texttt{LensObservations}.

column1: #     A separate table \texttt{LensOutliers} compiles all those observations that could not be associated to a component around a given sourceId
column2: and that have therefore been discarded from the analysis.

column1: #     How to cite and acknowledge Gaia:
#   description: The name of the gravitational lens candidate
#   description: Index of the component for this sourceId
#   description: Number of valid observations used for this component
#   description: Mean right ascension of the component
#   description: Standard deviation of the right ascension of the component
#   description: Mean declination of the clusters of measurements
#   description: Standard deviation of the declination measurements
#   description: Mean G flux of the component
#   description: Uncertainty of the mean flux value for this component
#   description: Mean onboard G magnitude of the component
